## Problema 19

A car pushes a stalled truck up a hill. The car exerts a force of magnitude $F_1$ on the truck. The truck exerts a force of magnitude $F_2$ on the car. Then

(A) $F_1 = F_2$ since these forces form an action-reaction pair.
(B) $F_1 = F_2$ only if the car and truck do not accelerate.
(C) $F_1 > F_2$, or else the car and the truck would not move.
(D) $F_1 < F_2$ because the truck is heavier.

**Topic:** [[Newtonian Mechanics]]
**Metodi:** [[Free-Body Diagram (metodo)|Free-Body Diagram]], [[Physical Modeling (metodo)|Physical Modeling]]
**Competenze:** [[Physical Reasoning (competenza)|Physical Reasoning]]
